; The helloworld app — a PLAIN dune project. `dune build` produces everything;
; `dune exec ./server.exe` runs it. The `fennec dev` CLI wraps these with
; livereload, but nothing here depends on the CLI existing.
;
; Asset pipeline = ordinary dune rules that call the `fennec` binary. esbuild and
; the CSS engine run via %{bin:fennec}; the outputs (app.css, app.js) are normal
; dune targets dropped next to server.exe, which reads them at startup. Because
; they are real targets, `dune build --watch` rebuilds them incrementally on edit,
; which is what drives livereload. Sources live in src/ so input and output names
; never collide.

; SCSS -> minified CSS. `fennec build` writes <base>.css, so src/app.scss -> app.css.
(rule
 (targets app.css)
 (deps src/app.scss)
 (action
  (run %{bin:fennec} build -o . src/app.scss)))

; JS -> bundled, minified app.js.
(rule
 (targets app.js)
 (deps src/app.js)
 (action
  (run %{bin:fennec} build -o . src/app.js)))

(executable
 (name server)
 (libraries fennec.core fennec.server eio eio_main routes unix))
